"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Add Phosphate-buffered saline buffer (PBS) with 1% formaldehyde (FAA)<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">1<\/span><span>.To detect histone modifications this is enough, but for protein binding we perform a dual crosslinking with DSG (disuccinimidyl glutarate) 2 mM.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":726626,"guid":"2EBC3AF0553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","previous_id":726625,"previous_guid":"2EBB0270553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"0138AAC3C3A44EF5820036C8A6408087","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Crosslinking"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"25C536CFCC704AF6B6E4BB13C2720302","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Crosslink in a desiccator attached to a vaccum pump for 5 + 5 min (for Arabidopsis seedlings) or 5 min + 10 min + 10 min (for Brassica leaves and inflorescences)<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">2<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":726627,"guid":"2EBCB020553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","previous_id":726626,"previous_guid":"2EBC3AF0553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"FADC6142CADB4634BFBBD390015F2369","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Crosslinking"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"550A6257F3A34D64B59C7E3F5C751055","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Stop the crosslinking by adding Glycine 2 M to a final concentration of 0.125M. (2.5 ml of 2M Glycine in 37ml of water), vacuum for 5 min.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":726628,"guid":"2EBCFE40553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","previous_id":726627,"previous_guid":"2EBCB020553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"364763699E974355A7E4E3EC68EE7604","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Crosslinking"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"B9197F6A7C7D459FBC3F20DE5268A051","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Remove the tissue from the vacuum and rinse off the formaldehyde with MilliQ water twice. Remove as much water as possible from the seedlings by placing on a paper towel.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":726629,"guid":"2EBD2550553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","previous_id":726628,"previous_guid":"2EBCFE40553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"103CFCDACEA44432B00F1F49D69D5911","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Crosslinking"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"9CCAF928EDA645BBAB5F828970F605EE","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Freeze in liquid nitrogen and store crosslinked tissue at -80\u00b0C<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":726631,"guid":"4DF53DE0553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","previous_id":726629,"previous_guid":"2EBD2550553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"0647955DD51D4394BAF89E2F66DC74D8","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Chromatin Extraction and Sonication"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"672006D0C1454E149A553FFDBD7C86CA","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Grind with mortar in liquid nitrogen to a fine powder.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#f8e71c","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":726632,"guid":"4E0D32B0553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","previous_id":726631,"previous_guid":"4DF53DE0553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"AB1BD0553CF8406C83697BE9F3C7D607","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Chromatin Extraction and Sonication"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"95BC4A26A6FF4DBF9CF56C3EC275D868","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Pass to a 50ml centrifuge tube and add the powder to 10 ml of Extraction Buffer 1. After adding buffer, ensure you mix well so all the tissue has dissolved into the buffer.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":726633,"guid":"4E0D32B1553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","previous_id":726632,"previous_guid":"4E0D32B0553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"8C13D2C874404A3480C4371A0F22DFB7","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Chromatin Extraction and Sonication"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"0C4FD66B0E1E4432BA259766FF0AB52D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Filter the solution through a layer of Miracloth into a 50ml centrifuge tube. Repeat step 9 until the solution is clear of big tissue particles.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":726634,"guid":"4E0D59C0553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","previous_id":726633,"previous_guid":"4E0D32B1553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"C82F51BF608F4DBEB2A2A3D45E93843D","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Chromatin Extraction and Sonication"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"0ECADCD681E54A94A2A60DB4A2B6CFDA","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Centrifuge at 5000 xg for 10 min at 4\u00b0C.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":726635,"guid":"4E0D80D0553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","previous_id":726634,"previous_guid":"4E0D59C0553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"20CA77BFC2234DA898A4583D662CA0E5","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Chromatin Extraction and Sonication"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"4410C0391F2541B286E48BA0BA373AF0","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Gently remove supernatant and resuspend the pellet in 1 ml of Extraction Buffer 2. Transfer the solution to 1.5ml centrifuge tube.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":726636,"guid":"4E0D80D1553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","previous_id":726635,"previous_guid":"4E0D80D0553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"ED20AE78F2CF474AB106FF140A1277AA","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Chromatin Extraction and Sonication"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"9B212347D7F14A6BB3DA5AA4DADDF815","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Centrifuge at 5000 xg for 10 min at 4\u00b0C.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":726637,"guid":"4E0D80D2553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","previous_id":726636,"previous_guid":"4E0D80D1553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"7633B08D17074EC687AC913BC091D47F","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Chromatin Extraction and Sonication"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"914B90DB5CA5479EA44ECBD9A10BD958","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Remove supernatant and resuspend pellet in 300 \u00b5l of Extraction Buffer 3.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":726638,"guid":"4E0DA7E0553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","previous_id":726637,"previous_guid":"4E0D80D2553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E0CD4B3455734A14AE45BD8F3FCD089B","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Chromatin Extraction and Sonication"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"6C1B3271FD174EFBA0F4EC219354A925","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">In a clean eppendorf, add 600 \u00b5l of Extraction Buffer 3. Take the 300 \u00b5l solution (resuspended pellet) from step 13 and carefully lay it on top of the clean 600 \u00b5l of Extraction Buffer 3.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":726639,"guid":"4E0DA7E1553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","previous_id":726638,"previous_guid":"4E0DA7E0553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"AE4AA751DABC45C183D50766D867163F","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Chromatin Extraction and Sonication"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"46118EAE912C483DAD44BE0438A09857","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Centrifuge at 16000 xg for 60min at 4 \u00b0C.At this point, it is advisable to prepare Nuclei Lysis Buffer and ChIP Dilution Buffer, to turn on the Bioruptor and to prepare the Dynabeads (go to step 20).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":726640,"guid":"4E817850553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","previous_id":726639,"previous_guid":"4E0DA7E1553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"9EC885013DB54DAD9787302320230D5E","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Chromatin Extraction and Sonication"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"90D4D6EE1D0C4ABFAC47BA64BD0022AC","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Remove the supernatant and resuspend the chromatin pellet in 200 \u00b5l of Nuclei Lysis Buffer<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">3<\/span><span>.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":726641,"guid":"4E9D8BD0553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","previous_id":726640,"previous_guid":"4E817850553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"85FB68CE98334513AFE19FF664D0999B","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Chromatin Extraction and Sonication"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"E74B16CFD9C6496DB61E7FB4603BFA7A","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Resuspend the pellet by pipetting up and down (keep solution cold). Take a 5 \u00b5l aliquot of each sample to check sonication efficiency<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">4<\/span><span>.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":726643,"guid":"4E9DD9F0553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","previous_id":730636,"previous_guid":"D6887C905F6711E9808A4599CF1E7615","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"4A32C45364034280A7152B8E7D9AB711","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"9B7B70CBBD294E77BE81B2AA72FF3A8B","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Spin chromatin solution at 2500 xg for 5 min at 4 \u00b0C to pellet debris.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":726669,"guid":"553A8F00554B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","previous_id":726643,"previous_guid":"4E9DD9F0553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"8A1D749DBAD24641AAA124AD425CC9BC","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Immunoprecipitation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"8E6E641F23424BF4B46AB3F7CDD3B39B","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Prepare the Dynabeads magnetic beads (Protein A for rabbit antibody or Protein G for mouse antibody). For each immunoprecipitation wash 15 \u00b5l Dynabeads in 500 \u00b5l ChIP dilution buffer twice. Then, add 1-5 \u00b5g of antibody and incubate the Dynabeads and the antibody in 50 \u00b5l ChIP Dilution Buffer rotating at 4\u00b0C for 1 h.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#d0021b","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":726670,"guid":"553ADD20554B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","previous_id":726669,"previous_guid":"553A8F00554B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"8DF8B8BFA8AC4F5893D4917369A1DD4D","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Immunoprecipitation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"C634CDE6A3A94B97BD3D4DFB5CD2C511","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Wash prepared antibody coated Dynabeads with 500 \u00b5l of ChIP dilution buffer. Let Dynabeads attach to the magnet. Then, discard buffer.Resuspend Dynabeads in 50\u00b5l of ChIP Dilution Buffer and keep aside on ice.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":726671,"guid":"553B5250554B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","previous_id":726670,"previous_guid":"553ADD20554B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"4EA58162E31C4732856106A5CDD11873","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Immunoprecipitation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"841E929CD3D0419CBB8FD92C745F1C72","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">For the immunoprecipitation, measure chromatin solution from step 19, usually ~150 \u00b5l. Take INPUT: 10% of the volume (15 \u00b5l) of chromatin and store it at -20\u00b0C.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":726672,"guid":"553BA070554B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","previous_id":726671,"previous_guid":"553B5250554B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"2533390D9A244F0784013DF006BD23E7","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Immunoprecipitation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"E12171F4310A43F596BA04437CE37D1A","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Dilute chromatin solution 10 times adding 1.5 ml of ChIP Dilution Buffer. The point here is to dilute the 1% SDS to 0.1% SDS with ChIP dilution buffer. This is enough for two immunoprecipitations or one immunoprecipitation and no-antibody control sample. For three immunoprecipitations is better to start from 300 \u00b5l of Nuclei Lysis Buffer (step 16).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":726675,"guid":"B8348A70554B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","previous_id":726681,"previous_guid":"129C7630554C11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"EEA56C6F12E1410AA3B03CA21CB16542","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA recovery"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"C768730EAC46479F8F86DF1FE6C34BCE","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">The next morning perform the washes using 1 ml of each buffer (see below).  Wash at 4\u00b0C for 5 min with gentle rotation and let beads attach to magnets in between washes. Use the sequence of buffers listed below:<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">a) Low Salt Wash Buffer: 2 washes.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">b) High Salt Wash Buffer: 1 wash (optional).<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">c) LiCl Wash Buffer: 1 wash (optional).<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">d) TE Buffer: 2 washes.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":726676,"guid":"B852C0D0554B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","previous_id":726675,"previous_guid":"B8348A70554B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"500B5D573A25450291D3C2840BDE91B7","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA recovery"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"9EF2E991DA3341A1B74B99C8CCF39F31","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Take the INPUTs frozen the day before and elute immune complexes and INPUTs by adding 200 \u00b5l 10% Chelex 100 resin (10g in 100ml water) and boil the samples at 98\u00b0C for 10min with agitation in a thermomixer.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":726677,"guid":"B852E7E0554B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","previous_id":726676,"previous_guid":"B852C0D0554B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"D487754F970E40349981DB50D1654C78","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA recovery"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"9089BD51837D472E8664AF8A8F0C7E00","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Cool in ice and incubate with 2 \u00b5l Proteinase K (10 mg\/ml) at 37\u00b0C for 20min.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":726678,"guid":"B852E7E1554B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","previous_id":726677,"previous_guid":"B852E7E0554B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"6F84592108B24AE48BD15A195BE9AB5B","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA recovery"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"878422842EE5468493E5E369A471CB12","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Boil samples again at 98\u00b0C for 10 min with agitation in thermomixer to inactivate Proteinase K.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":726679,"guid":"B8530EF0554B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","previous_id":726678,"previous_guid":"B852E7E1554B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"389E7F9233EE4900BC19AB5D0462EC26","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA recovery"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"3CA3845478554DBB8ED67E08B6002411","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Cool in ice and spin the tubes in microcentrifuge at 16000 xg for 5 min at 4\u00b0C. Transfer ~160 \u00b5l of the supernatant to a new DNA low binding microtube. Do not take any Chelex particle. Store at 4\u00b0C or at 20-\u00b0C for long term storage.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":726680,"guid":"B8530EF1554B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","previous_id":726679,"previous_guid":"B8530EF0554B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"664258FDADB94CDCA38F84F7D3033456","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA recovery"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"789DC39D172C4D9DAFA97CB23EC9AEA3","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>For real-time quantitative PCR analysis, ChIP DNA can be used directly but INPUT DNA must be diluted at least 1:10 in water<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">7<\/span><span>. Usually 1-2 \u00b5l of the DNA solution is enough for PCR amplification.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":726681,"guid":"129C7630554C11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","previous_id":726672,"previous_guid":"553BA070554B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"EFFB6B05D074487DB159861A00F91076","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Immunoprecipitation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"F9ACFCFC69D44C1BA2FB978AB1D70089","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Add antibody coated Dynabeads into the 750 \u00b5l of chromatin solution in a DNA low binding microtube. Incubate the immunoprecipitation rotating at 4\u00b0C overnight<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">6<\/span><span>.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":730636,"guid":"D6887C905F6711E9808A4599CF1E7615","previous_id":726641,"previous_guid":"4E9D8BD0553B11E98C81D584EF33B9AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"2F0EA30191C54AD1A986B0BEEC42E2B5","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"F34FB9BAB91F46979C600EADD4884171","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Sonicate the chromatin solution for 20 min (30sec on\/off intervals) HIGH setting<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">5<\/span><span> (LOW setting protein ChIPs) in the Bioruptor (sonicator water bath must be pre-cooled). Take a 5\u00b5l aliquot of each sample to check sonication efficiency<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">4<\/span><span>.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:justify\"><span>Chromatin Immunoprecipitation (ChIP) is a crucial technique to study chromatin regulation, epigenetic phenomena and transcription factor DNA-binding in vivo. This technique is widely used in model plant systems like Arabidopsis but reliability in other plant systems is challenging. We adapted our well-established Arabidopsis ChIP protocol to be used with leaves and inflorescences of Brassica crops species (<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Brassica rapa<\/span><span> and <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Brassica napus<\/span><span>). This protocol was originally based on Gendrel et al. <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Nature Methods <\/span><span>volume 2, pages 213\u2013218 (2005), but has several modifications inlcluding chromatin sonication using a BioRuptor (Diagenode), immunoprecipitation using magnetic Dynabeads (Thermofisher) and DNA elution recovery performed using Chelex 100 (Bio Rad). The protocol is quick and very reproducible and has been validated against a number of histone modifications and protein tag antibodies.<\/span><\/div><style>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t  .justify:after {\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t    content: \"\";\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t    display:inline-block;\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t    width: 100%;\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t  }\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/style><\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1562061878}